The paper deals with enumerative coding and error correction strategies for Grassmann codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) communities. The paper also discusses efficient methods for enumerating pointsets in Grassmannians, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies these techniques to line polar Grassmann codes, which have applications in systems and control theory (cs.SY).
